<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="478" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1709,2024]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1745,1771]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Habitat.</emphasis>
Very little information exists regarding the habitat associations of this species. Almost all specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1911" box="[183,359,1781,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Horvathinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelocoroides">
<emphasis box="[183,359,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">H. pelocoroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently known have been captured while flying attracted to lights (
<bibRefCitation author="Schnack, J. A. &amp; Estevez, A. L." box="[1138,1432,1781,1808]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="21 - 27" refId="ref57848" refString="Schnack, J. A. &amp; Estevez, A. L. (2005) On the taxonomic status of the genus Horvathinia Montandon (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 21 - 27." type="journal article" year="2005">Schnack &amp; Estévez 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues, C. L. &amp; Braga, R. B. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F." box="[151,398,1817,1843]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="298 - 300" refId="ref57186" refString="Rodrigues, C. L., Braga, R. B. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. (2020) Rediscovery of the holotype of Horvathinia lenti De Carlo, 1958, new junior synonym of H. pelocoroides Montadon, 1911 (Insecta: Hemiptera: Belostomatidae). Zootaxa, 4750 (2), 298 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4750.2.14" type="journal article" year="2020">
Rodrigues 
<emphasis box="[274,330,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeida, T. M. de &amp; Stefanello, F. &amp; Hamada, N." box="[415,657,1817,1843]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="20195906" refId="ref45152" refString="Almeida, T. M. de, Stefanello, F. &amp; Hamada, N. (2019) Belostomatidae (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha) held in the invertebrate collection of the Instituto Nacional de Pesquisas da Amazonia, Manaus, Brazil: inventory and new distributional records. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 59, e 20195906. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 1807 - 0205 / 2019.59.06" type="journal article" year="2019">
Almeida 
<emphasis box="[519,575,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
examined material from the Guaporé River (
<collectingRegion box="[1163,1340,1817,1843]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Rondônia State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1351,1424,1817,1844]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). Although sampling methods were not mentioned in the text, we believe this material has also been taken at lights together with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Montandon, 1899)" baseAuthorityName="Montandon" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[306,809,1889,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurivillianum">
<emphasis box="[306,583,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Belostoma aurivillianum</emphasis>
(Montandon, 1899)
</taxonomicName>
, collected with light trap in the same place (see p. 5, under “Material examined”). In wetland habitats, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1911" box="[674,847,1925,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Horvathinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelocoroides">
<emphasis box="[674,847,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">H. pelocoroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected from marshes densely filled with floating hydrophytes dominated by 
<taxonomicName box="[547,782,1961,1987]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Pontederia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[547,782,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Pontederia crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[835,1010,1962,1987]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Pistia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stratiotes">
<emphasis box="[835,1010,1962,1987]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Pistia stratiotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a permanent shallow pond (Laguna Don Blanco) in 
<collectingRegion box="[331,556,1997,2023]" country="Argentina" name="Corrientes" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">Corrientes Province</collectingRegion>
, Argentina (
<bibRefCitation author="Schnack, J. A. &amp; Estevez, A. L. &amp; Armua de Reyes, A. C." box="[692,920,1997,2024]" pageId="26" pageNumber="477" pagination="197 - 202" refId="ref57887" refString="Schnack, J. A., Estevez, A. L. &amp; Armua de Reyes, A. C. (2006) Laguna Don Blanco, Argentina: first record of Horvathinia (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae) as a wetland dweller. Entomological News, 117, 197 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.3157 / 0013 - 872 X (2006) 117 [197: LDBAFR] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">
Schnack 
<emphasis box="[796,852,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="477">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,150,250]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
At the INR, specimens were taken at lights in 
<collectingRegion box="[729,818,151,177]" country="Uruguay" name="Colonia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Colonia</collectingRegion>
Carlos Pellegrini (
<bibRefCitation author="Schnack, J. A. &amp; Estevez, A. L." box="[1032,1323,150,177]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" pagination="21 - 27" refId="ref57848" refString="Schnack, J. A. &amp; Estevez, A. L. (2005) On the taxonomic status of the genus Horvathinia Montandon (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 21 - 27." type="journal article" year="2005">Schnack &amp; Estévez 2005</bibRefCitation>
), and collected in association with 
<taxonomicName box="[439,570,187,212]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Pistia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stratiotes">
<emphasis box="[439,570,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">P. stratiotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[584,715,187,213]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Salviniaceae" genus="Salvinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Salviniales" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[584,676,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Salvinia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[727,874,187,213]" class="Liliopsida" family="Hydrocharitaceae" genus="Egeria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="densa">
<emphasis box="[727,874,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Egeria densa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1058,187,212]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Pontederia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[927,1058,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">P. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Laguna Iberá (
<bibRefCitation author="Armua, A. C. &amp; Estevez, A. L. &amp; Kehr, A. I. &amp; Benitez, M. E." pageId="27" pageNumber="478" pagination="9 - 12" refId="ref45465" refString="Armua, A. C., Estevez, A. L., Kehr, A. I. &amp; Benitez, M. E. (2011) Nueva cita de Horvathinia pelocoroides Montandon (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae) para la provincia de Corrientes, Argentina. Facena, 27, 9 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / fac. 270925" type="journal article" year="2011">
Armúa 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Armua de Reyes, A. C. &amp; Estevez, A. L." box="[219,597,223,250]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" pagination="222 - 225" refId="ref45662" refString="Armua de Reyes, A. C. &amp; Estevez, A. L. (2016) Nuevos hallazgos de hemiptera (Belostomatidae) para la provincia de Corrientes, Argentina. Extensionismo, Innovacion y Transferencia Tecnologica, 3, 222 - 225. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / eitt. 303023" type="journal article" year="2016">Armúa de Reyes &amp; Estévez 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
